      "beast_suffix": "",
      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Root issues, like those caused by compaction or root rot, can definitely present as nutrient deficiencies, even if the soil chemistry seems fine. Poor drainage, for instance, suffocates the roots, preventing them from absorbing anything properly. You might also have overly sandy soil that drains too fast, causing nutrients to simply wash away before the bush can use them. A good soil structure is crucial; if it's too dense or too loose, the roots struggle to breathe and anchor themselves.",
      "source": "target",
